== Births == * {{ill|Tenryaku|ja|天暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|950 AD|ja|950th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 12|ja|6月12日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Emperor Reisō|ja|冷泉天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , the 63rd {{ill|Emperor|ja|天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (d. {{ill|1011 AD|ja|1011th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Gennin|ja|元永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1118 AD|ja|1118th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 14|ja|6月14日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Chiba Tsunetane|ja|千葉常胤|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a military commander and protector (shugo) of {{ill|Shimōsa Province|ja|下総国|lt=Shimōsa|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (d. {{ill|1201 AD|ja|1201st year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Shōhō|ja|正保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1644 AD|ja|1644th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 28|ja|6月28日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Tsunashige|ja|徳川綱重|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , the first lord of the {{ill|Kōfu Domain|ja|甲府藩|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , the third son of {{ill|Tokugawa Iemitsu|ja|徳川家光|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , and the father of {{ill|Tokugawa Ienobu|ja|徳川家宣|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (d. {{ill|1678 AD|ja|1678th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Kōka|ja|弘化|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd Year (leap May) ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1846 AD|ja|1846th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|July 17|ja|7月17日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Iemoto|ja|徳川家茂|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , the 14th shogun of the {{ill|Edo Shogunate|ja|Tokugawa shogunate|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (d. {{ill|1866 AD|ja|1866th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1871 AD|ja|1871st year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|July 11|ja|7月11日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Kida Sadakichi|ja|喜田貞吉|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a historian (d. {{ill|1939 AD|ja|1939th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 13th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1636 AD|ja|1636th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 27|ja|6月27日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Date Masamune|ja|伊達政宗|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a military commander and the first lord of the {{ill|Sendai Domain|ja|仙台藩|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (born {{ill|1567 AD|ja|1567th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
