== Events == * {{ill|Emperor Monmu|ja|文武天皇}} 3rd Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} {{ill|699 AD|ja|699th year}} {{ill|June 26|ja|6月26日}} ) – The founder of Shugendō, {{ill|En no Ozunu|ja|役行者|lt=En no Ozunu|lt_ja=役小角}} , was exiled to {{ill|Izu Province|ja|Izu Province|lt=Izu|lt_ja=伊豆}} due to slander from his disciples. * {{ill|Bunji|ja|文治}} 1st Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} {{ill|1185 AD|ja|1185th year}} {{ill|June 23|ja|6月23日}} ) – To appease {{ill|Minamoto no Yoritomo|ja|源頼朝}} , {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshitsune|ja|源義経|lt=Yoshitsune|lt_ja=義経}} , who was en route to Kamakura, was detained at {{ill|Koshigoe|ja|腰越}} , and thus entrusted a letter (the {{ill|Koshigoe Letter|ja|腰越状}} ) to {{ill|Ōe Hiromoto|ja|大江広元}} . * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era}} 4th Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} {{ill|1576 AD|ja|1576th year}} {{ill|June 20|ja|6月20日}} ) – {{ill|Maeda Toshiie|ja|Maeda Toshiie}} executed approximately 1,000 captives of the {{ill|Echizen Ikko-ikki|ja|越前一向一揆}} , subjecting them to crucifixion and boiling. (Dating based on Ikko-ikki inscription tiles is approximate; some sources propose Tenshō 8 ({{ill|1580 AD|ja|1580th year}} {{ill|July 5|ja|7月5日}} )). * {{ill|Kansei|ja|Kansei}} 2nd Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1790 AD|ja|1790th year}} {{ill|July 6|ja|7月6日}} ) – The Kansei Prohibition on Heterodox Learning was enacted, with {{ill|Matsudaira Sadanobu|ja|松平定信}} banning the teaching of subjects other than {{ill|Neo-Confucianism|ja|朱子学}} at {{ill|Yushima Seidō|ja|湯島聖堂}} .
== Births == * {{ill|Tenryaku|ja|天暦}} 4th Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} {{ill|950 AD|ja|950th year}} {{ill|June 12|ja|6月12日}} ) – {{ill|Emperor Reisō|ja|冷泉天皇}} , the 63rd {{ill|Emperor|ja|天皇}} (d. {{ill|1011 AD|ja|1011th year}} ). * {{ill|Gennin|ja|元永}} 1st Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} {{ill|1118 AD|ja|1118th year}} {{ill|June 14|ja|6月14日}} ) – {{ill|Chiba Tsunetane|ja|千葉常胤}} , a military commander and protector (shugo) of {{ill|Shimōsa Province|ja|下総国|lt=Shimōsa}} (d. {{ill|1201 AD|ja|1201st year}} ). * {{ill|Shōhō|ja|正保}} 1st Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1644 AD|ja|1644th year}} {{ill|June 28|ja|6月28日}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Tsunashige|ja|徳川綱重}} , the first lord of the {{ill|Kōfu Domain|ja|甲府藩}} , the third son of {{ill|Tokugawa Iemitsu|ja|徳川家光}} , and the father of {{ill|Tokugawa Ienobu|ja|徳川家宣}} (d. {{ill|1678 AD|ja|1678th year}} ). * {{ill|Kōka|ja|弘化}} 3rd Year (leap May) ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1846 AD|ja|1846th year}} {{ill|July 17|ja|7月17日}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Iemoto|ja|徳川家茂}} , the 14th shogun of the {{ill|Edo Shogunate|ja|Tokugawa shogunate}} (d. {{ill|1866 AD|ja|1866th year}} ). * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era}} 4th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1871 AD|ja|1871st year}} {{ill|July 11|ja|7月11日}} ) – {{ill|Kida Sadakichi|ja|喜田貞吉}} , a historian (d. {{ill|1939 AD|ja|1939th year}} ).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永}} 13th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1636 AD|ja|1636th year}} {{ill|June 27|ja|6月27日}} ) – {{ill|Date Masamune|ja|伊達政宗}} , a military commander and the first lord of the {{ill|Sendai Domain|ja|仙台藩}} (born {{ill|1567 AD|ja|1567th year}} ).
