== Events == * {{ill|Emperor Monmu|ja|文武天皇|qq=}} 3rd Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} {{ill|699 AD|ja|699th year|qq=}} {{ill|June 26|ja|6月26日|qq=}} ) – The founder of Shugendō, {{ill|En no Ozunu|ja|役行者|lt=En no Ozunu|lt_ja=役小角|qq=}} , was exiled to {{ill|Izu Province|ja|Izu Province|lt=Izu|lt_ja=伊豆|qq=}} due to slander from his disciples. * {{ill|Bunji|ja|文治|qq=}} 1st Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} {{ill|1185 AD|ja|1185th year|qq=}} {{ill|June 23|ja|6月23日|qq=}} ) – To appease {{ill|Minamoto no Yoritomo|ja|源頼朝|qq=}} , {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshitsune|ja|源義経|lt=Yoshitsune|lt_ja=義経|qq=}} , who was en route to Kamakura, was detained at {{ill|Koshigoe|ja|腰越|qq=}} , and thus entrusted a letter (the {{ill|Koshigoe Letter|ja|腰越状|qq=}} ) to {{ill|Ōe Hiromoto|ja|大江広元|qq=}} . * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|qq=}} 4th Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} {{ill|1576 AD|ja|1576th year|qq=}} {{ill|June 20|ja|6月20日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Maeda Toshiie|ja|Maeda Toshiie|qq=}} executed approximately 1,000 captives of the {{ill|Echizen Ikko-ikki|ja|越前一向一揆|qq=}} , subjecting them to crucifixion and boiling. (Dating based on Ikko-ikki inscription tiles is approximate; some sources propose Tenshō 8 ({{ill|1580 AD|ja|1580th year|qq=}} {{ill|July 5|ja|7月5日|qq=}} )). * {{ill|Kansei|ja|Kansei|qq=}} 2nd Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} {{ill|1790 AD|ja|1790th year|qq=}} {{ill|July 6|ja|7月6日|qq=}} ) – The Kansei Prohibition on Heterodox Learning was enacted, with {{ill|Matsudaira Sadanobu|ja|松平定信|qq=}} banning the teaching of subjects other than {{ill|Neo-Confucianism|ja|朱子学|qq=}} at {{ill|Yushima Seidō|ja|湯島聖堂|qq=}} .
== Births == * {{ill|Tenryaku|ja|天暦|qq=}} 4th Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} {{ill|950 AD|ja|950th year|qq=}} {{ill|June 12|ja|6月12日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Emperor Reisō|ja|冷泉天皇|qq=}} , the 63rd {{ill|Emperor|ja|天皇|qq=}} (d. {{ill|1011 AD|ja|1011th year|qq=}} ). * {{ill|Gennin|ja|元永|qq=}} 1st Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} {{ill|1118 AD|ja|1118th year|qq=}} {{ill|June 14|ja|6月14日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Chiba Tsunetane|ja|千葉常胤|qq=}} , a military commander and protector (shugo) of {{ill|Shimōsa Province|ja|下総国|lt=Shimōsa|qq=}} (d. {{ill|1201 AD|ja|1201st year|qq=}} ). * {{ill|Shōhō|ja|正保|qq=}} 1st Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} {{ill|1644 AD|ja|1644th year|qq=}} {{ill|June 28|ja|6月28日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Tsunashige|ja|徳川綱重|qq=}} , the first lord of the {{ill|Kōfu Domain|ja|甲府藩|qq=}} , the third son of {{ill|Tokugawa Iemitsu|ja|徳川家光|qq=}} , and the father of {{ill|Tokugawa Ienobu|ja|徳川家宣|qq=}} (d. {{ill|1678 AD|ja|1678th year|qq=}} ). * {{ill|Kōka|ja|弘化|qq=}} 3rd Year (leap May) ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} {{ill|1846 AD|ja|1846th year|qq=}} {{ill|July 17|ja|7月17日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Iemoto|ja|徳川家茂|qq=}} , the 14th shogun of the {{ill|Edo Shogunate|ja|Tokugawa shogunate|qq=}} (d. {{ill|1866 AD|ja|1866th year|qq=}} ). * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=}} 4th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} {{ill|1871 AD|ja|1871st year|qq=}} {{ill|July 11|ja|7月11日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Kida Sadakichi|ja|喜田貞吉|qq=}} , a historian (d. {{ill|1939 AD|ja|1939th year|qq=}} ).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永|qq=}} 13th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} {{ill|1636 AD|ja|1636th year|qq=}} {{ill|June 27|ja|6月27日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Date Masamune|ja|伊達政宗|qq=}} , a military commander and the first lord of the {{ill|Sendai Domain|ja|仙台藩|qq=}} (born {{ill|1567 AD|ja|1567th year|qq=}} ).
