{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=五月廿四|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 5월 24일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar May|qq=}} '''May 24''' is the 24th day of month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|qq=|qq=draft}} the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|qq=|qq=draft}} .
== Events == * {{ill|Emperor Monmu|ja|文武天皇|qq=|qq=draft}} 3rd Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|699 AD|ja|699th year|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|June 26|ja|6月26日|qq=|qq=draft}} ) – The founder of Shugendō, {{ill|En no Ozunu|ja|役行者|lt=En no Ozunu|lt_ja=役小角|qq=|qq=draft}} , was exiled to {{ill|Izu Province|ja|Izu Province|lt=Izu|lt_ja=伊豆|qq=|qq=draft}} due to slander from his disciples. * {{ill|Bunji|ja|文治|qq=|qq=draft}} 1st Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|1185 AD|ja|1185th year|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|June 23|ja|6月23日|qq=|qq=draft}} ) – To appease {{ill|Minamoto no Yoritomo|ja|源頼朝|qq=|qq=draft}} , {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshitsune|ja|源義経|lt=Yoshitsune|lt_ja=義経|qq=|qq=draft}} , who was en route to Kamakura, was detained at {{ill|Koshigoe|ja|腰越|qq=|qq=draft}} , and thus entrusted a letter (the {{ill|Koshigoe Letter|ja|腰越状|qq=|qq=draft}} ) to {{ill|Ōe Hiromoto|ja|大江広元|qq=|qq=draft}} . * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|qq=|qq=draft}} 4th Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|1576 AD|ja|1576th year|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|June 20|ja|6月20日|qq=|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Maeda Toshiie|ja|Maeda Toshiie|qq=|qq=draft}} executed approximately 1,000 captives of the {{ill|Echizen Ikko-ikki|ja|越前一向一揆|qq=|qq=draft}} , subjecting them to crucifixion and boiling. (Dating based on Ikko-ikki inscription tiles is approximate; some sources propose Tenshō 8 ({{ill|1580 AD|ja|1580th year|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|July 5|ja|7月5日|qq=|qq=draft}} )). * {{ill|Kansei|ja|Kansei|qq=|qq=draft}} 2nd Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|1790 AD|ja|1790th year|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|July 6|ja|7月6日|qq=|qq=draft}} ) – The Kansei Prohibition on Heterodox Learning was enacted, with {{ill|Matsudaira Sadanobu|ja|松平定信|qq=|qq=draft}} banning the teaching of subjects other than {{ill|Neo-Confucianism|ja|朱子学|qq=|qq=draft}} at {{ill|Yushima Seidō|ja|湯島聖堂|qq=|qq=draft}} .
== Births == * {{ill|Tenryaku|ja|天暦|qq=|qq=draft}} 4th Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|950 AD|ja|950th year|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|June 12|ja|6月12日|qq=|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Emperor Reisō|ja|冷泉天皇|qq=|qq=draft}} , the 63rd {{ill|Emperor|ja|天皇|qq=|qq=draft}} (d. {{ill|1011 AD|ja|1011th year|qq=|qq=draft}} ). * {{ill|Gennin|ja|元永|qq=|qq=draft}} 1st Year ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|1118 AD|ja|1118th year|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|June 14|ja|6月14日|qq=|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Chiba Tsunetane|ja|千葉常胤|qq=|qq=draft}} , a military commander and protector (shugo) of {{ill|Shimōsa Province|ja|下総国|lt=Shimōsa|qq=|qq=draft}} (d. {{ill|1201 AD|ja|1201st year|qq=|qq=draft}} ). * {{ill|Shōhō|ja|正保|qq=|qq=draft}} 1st Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|1644 AD|ja|1644th year|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|June 28|ja|6月28日|qq=|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Tsunashige|ja|徳川綱重|qq=|qq=draft}} , the first lord of the {{ill|Kōfu Domain|ja|甲府藩|qq=|qq=draft}} , the third son of {{ill|Tokugawa Iemitsu|ja|徳川家光|qq=|qq=draft}} , and the father of {{ill|Tokugawa Ienobu|ja|徳川家宣|qq=|qq=draft}} (d. {{ill|1678 AD|ja|1678th year|qq=|qq=draft}} ). * {{ill|Kōka|ja|弘化|qq=|qq=draft}} 3rd Year (leap May) ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|1846 AD|ja|1846th year|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|July 17|ja|7月17日|qq=|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Iemoto|ja|徳川家茂|qq=|qq=draft}} , the 14th shogun of the {{ill|Edo Shogunate|ja|Tokugawa shogunate|qq=|qq=draft}} (d. {{ill|1866 AD|ja|1866th year|qq=|qq=draft}} ). * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|qq=draft}} 4th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|1871 AD|ja|1871st year|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|July 11|ja|7月11日|qq=|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Kida Sadakichi|ja|喜田貞吉|qq=|qq=draft}} , a historian (d. {{ill|1939 AD|ja|1939th year|qq=|qq=draft}} ).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永|qq=|qq=draft}} 13th Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|1636 AD|ja|1636th year|qq=|qq=draft}} {{ill|June 27|ja|6月27日|qq=|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Date Masamune|ja|伊達政宗|qq=|qq=draft}} , a military commander and the first lord of the {{ill|Sendai Domain|ja|仙台藩|qq=|qq=draft}} (born {{ill|1567 AD|ja|1567th year|qq=|qq=draft}} ).
