i link invalid}} executed approximately 1,000 captives of the {{ill|Echizen Ikko-ikki|ja|越前一向一揆|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Echizen Ikko-ikki|1=Echizen ikki|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11636409}} , subjecting them to crucifixion and boiling. (Dating based on Ikko-ikki inscription tiles is approximate; some sources propose Tenshō 8 ({{ill|1580|en|1580|qid=Q6712|lt=1580 AD|1=1580}} {{ill|July 5|en|July 5|qid=Q2696|lt=July 5|1=July 5}} )). * [[Kansei]]{{efn|January 1789 through February 1801|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kansei|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 2nd Year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1790|en|1790|qid=Q7775|lt=1790 AD|1=1790}} {{ill|July 6|en|July 6|qid=Q2695|lt=July 6|1=July 6}} ) – The Kansei Prohibition on Heterodox Learning was enacted, with {{ill|Matsudaira Sadanobu|en|Matsudaira Sadanobu|qid=Q284038|lt=Matsudaira Sadanobu|1=Matsudaira Sadanobu}} banning the teaching of subjects other than {{ill|Cheng–Zhu school|en|Cheng–Zhu school|qid=Q841735|lt=Neo-Confucianism|1=Cheng–Zhu school}} at {{ill|Yushima Seidō|en|Yushima Seidō|qid=Q1760591|lt=Yushima Seidō|1=Yushima Seidō}} .
